share_info.desc: Mr Funky56’s comment: the environmental legal way to off load septic waste from any ship is when they berth at any port depending on the size of their holding tanks for septic they have to use local council Registered waste removalist which involves running 6inch hoses from the ship holding tanks pumping to the 20 000litre tankers waiting on port and they usually do this at ports with the correct gear and facilities to accommodate the waste materials but watching this video they may have a problem with the storage tanks hence being a health and safety hazard to the people on board the cruise liner so discharging at sea is very uncommon but it can happen
